  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "jtidy security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for jtidy is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "JTidy is the Java port for HTML Tidy, which is an HTML syntax checker and a nice printer. JTidy can be used as a tool to clean up misformatted HTML. In addition, JTidy provides a DOM interface to the documents being processed, effectively enabling you to use JTidy as a DOM parser for real HTML.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nAn issue was discovered jtidy thru r938 allows attackers to cause a denial of service or other unspecified impacts via crafted object that uses cyclic dependencies.(CVE-2023-34623)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for jtidy is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2,openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP3,openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4,openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of high. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "High",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "jtidy",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
